00:05:45,742 --> 00:05:50,084
an NDA. These contracts have teeth just like the cock a

131
00:05:50,084 --> 00:05:54,886
demon. So what do we want to put in one of these? First off, you

132
00:05:54,886 --> 00:05:58,748
need to know if it's going to be a mutual NDA or a one way NDA.

133
00:05:58,748 --> 00:06:02,230
Meaning are we both sharing information or is only one

134
00:06:02,230 --> 00:06:04,311
person receiving that information and the other one

135
00:06:04,311 --> 00:06:04,651
sharing it?

136
00:06:05,050 --> 00:06:09,255
But the core of an NDA is going to be the definition of confidential information.

137
00:06:09,255 --> 00:06:10,236
You're sharing some stuff.

138
00:06:10,236 --> 00:06:11,377
Well, what is that stuff?

139
00:06:11,377 --> 00:06:12,538
How broad is that definition?

140
00:06:12,538 --> 00:06:13,759
Everything I tell you?

141
00:06:13,759 --> 00:06:14,920
Or is it narrow?

142
00:06:14,920 --> 00:06:16,502
And do I have to mark it?

143
00:06:16,502 --> 00:06:19,825
Is it going to be saying confidential on the top of every document?

144
00:06:19,825 --> 00:06:21,227
What happens if I tell you on Skype?

145
00:06:21,227 --> 00:06:22,608
Do I have to email you later?

146
00:06:22,608 --> 00:06:23,890
These are things you have to consider.

147
00:06:24,657 --> 00:06:27,678
You then have to think about what the permitted uses are.

148
00:06:27,678 --> 00:06:29,818
So what can they do with this information?

149
00:06:29,818 --> 00:06:31,859
Are they signing the end age just so that they can look

150
00:06:31,859 --> 00:06:33,980
over your stuff and decide if they want to work with you and

151
00:06:33,980 --> 00:06:35,680
they're not allowed to use it for any other purpose?

152
00:06:35,680 --> 00:06:38,741
Or is this something where you're working together and

153
00:06:38,741 --> 00:06:39,881
they're going to put it into a game?

154
00:06:39,881 --> 00:06:43,582
And finally, you need to know what their obligations are for

155
00:06:43,582 --> 00:06:44,322
keeping it secret.

156
00:06:44,322 --> 00:06:45,422
How long does it last?

157
00:06:45,422 --> 00:06:47,683
Is it for a year or is this to their grave?

158
00:06:47,683 --> 00:06:48,863
And who can they tell?

159
00:06:48,863 --> 00:06:51,084
How narrowly do they have to keep this information from

160
00:06:51,084 --> 00:06:51,864
their employees?

161
00:06:53,188 --> 00:06:55,410
Finally, a couple of practical concerns.

162
00:06:55,410 --> 00:06:57,472
First off, they can just say no.

163
00:06:57,472 --> 00:06:59,873
Not everyone's gonna agree to sign an NDA,

164
00:06:59,873 --> 00:07:02,635
so then you still have to decide if you wanna tell them.

165
00:07:02,635 --> 00:07:05,977
And, like I said before, enforcing costs time and money.

166
00:07:05,977 --> 00:07:06,678
It's not magical.

167
00:07:06,678 --> 00:07:09,280
They're not gonna be forced to not say anything.

168
00:07:09,280 --> 00:07:10,801
They could still disclose this stuff.

169
00:07:12,153 --> 00:07:14,313
So let's move on to our second contract,

170
00:07:14,313 --> 00:07:15,714
work for hire agreements.

171
00:07:15,714 --> 00:07:18,515
These are incredibly important, and they're between a

172
00:07:18,515 --> 00:07:22,436
developer and a contractor, or really anyone that's

173
00:07:22,436 --> 00:07:25,377
contributing something to a game, which actually includes

174
00:07:25,377 --> 00:07:26,617
the owners of a studio.

175
00:07:26,617 --> 00:07:29,058
There's a related type of agreement called an invention

176
00:07:29,058 --> 00:07:30,659
assignment agreement.

177
00:07:30,659 --> 00:07:33,799
And the owners need to sign this, as well as contractors

178
00:07:33,799 --> 00:07:36,360
signing work for hire agreements, because.

179
00:07:36,545 --> 00:07:41,188
This is the agreement that allows the studio to own the IP

180
00:07:41,188 --> 00:07:45,210
that's created. Brief copyright lesson. The default rule is

181
00:07:45,210 --> 00:07:47,652
that if someone creates something, they own that

182
00:07:47,652 --> 00:07:50,454
copyright. Meaning your artist owns the art, your sound person

183
00:07:50,454 --> 00:07:53,616
owns their sound, coder owns the code. Unless you have this

184
00:07:53,616 --> 00:07:56,718
exception, which is that it's work for hire and you need this

185
00:07:56,718 --> 00:07:59,100
written signed agreement to accomplish that in most cases.

186
00:07:59,100 --> 00:08:03,422
It also helps with some tax issues, but I would say ask

187
00:08:03,422 --> 00:08:05,023
your accountant. I don't do tax.

188
00:08:06,403 --> 00:08:08,544
These can absolutely lead to disasters.

189
00:08:08,544 --> 00:08:11,947
I've dealt with clients who've had games pulled from Steam

190
00:08:11,947 --> 00:08:14,209
and an angry former contractor with a bad

