00:08:15,810 --> 00:08:17,671
I've seen very expensive fights

193
00:08:17,671 --> 00:08:20,593
where they've had to pay people off.

194
00:08:20,593 --> 00:08:22,955
You just wanna make sure that it's clean

195
00:08:22,955 --> 00:08:25,217
and clear up front to avoid this.

196
00:08:25,832 --> 00:08:27,233
So how do we make that happen?

197
00:08:27,233 --> 00:08:29,835
Well, first off, we got to look at the IP rights section.

198
00:08:29,835 --> 00:08:31,796
It's called work for hire agreement

199
00:08:31,796 --> 00:08:34,398
because it sets up this work for hire arrangement

200
00:08:34,398 --> 00:08:37,039
where the company is the owner of the IP.

201
00:08:37,039 --> 00:08:38,980
You also want a little backup clause that says,

202
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:41,542
look, if for some reason a court doesn't agree to that,

203
00:08:41,542 --> 00:08:42,503
then you agree to assign it.

204
00:08:42,503 --> 00:08:44,564
One way or another, company owns it.

205
00:08:45,151 --> 00:08:50,832
There might be an exception if an artist wants a license to display things in their portfolio,

206
00:08:50,832 --> 00:08:55,713
and that's fine, but just make sure that you have some control over when they do that and what they display.

207
00:08:55,713 --> 00:08:58,634
