208
00:08:58,634 --> 00:09:01,874
Then you gotta figure out how you're gonna pay this person.

209
00:09:01,874 --> 00:09:08,196
Normally, you'd pay them either hourly or maybe with milestones, maybe there's a cap,

210
00:09:08,196 --> 00:09:11,497
or with rev share, which is quite popular among indies.

211
00:09:12,479 --> 00:09:15,202
Let's take a little bit to talk about RevShare,

212
00:09:15,202 --> 00:09:17,064
because this comes up a lot.

213
00:09:17,064 --> 00:09:21,669
RevShare's fine, but you can't just say 10% of the game.

214
00:09:21,669 --> 00:09:23,411
That doesn't mean anything.

215
00:09:23,411 --> 00:09:27,595
You need to think of a couple of key details here.

216
00:09:27,595 --> 00:09:28,817
First, 10% of what?

217
00:09:29,517 --> 00:09:30,819
What is net revenue?

218
00:09:30,819 --> 00:09:32,240
So what are you deducting from that?

219
00:09:32,240 --> 00:09:34,682
Is this before Steam's cut, after Steam's cut?

220
00:09:34,682 --> 00:09:36,764
What happens if a publisher's involved?

221
00:09:36,764 --> 00:09:37,865
Those sorts of things.

222
00:09:37,865 --> 00:09:40,708
Then you need to think about whether this

